Rating: 4
Really delicious with fresh, summer corn. Used a bunt pan to cut the corn from the cob, which makes everything so easy. It's really important to scrape all that milky starch out too. Mine was thick at first, but it's easy to modulate with more/less water. I also did not strain the pureed corn. We served this under scallops.

