Rating: 3
This was so good! I used five ears of corn (on sale), no sugar, a half-teaspoon of salt and a teaspoon of cornstarch and it came out perfectly. And I also didn't strain the corn, the crunchy bits and scrummy texture of the corn made the dish even better. And it's so easy to make! YUM! Into the recipe box it goes.

Rating: 4
Make sure you get the freshest sweetest corn available. It makes a huge difference in the taste. I've made this dish several times for dinner & all my guests rave about it. NOTE: once I forgot to use unsalted butter and the dish turned out too salty. Make sure you use unsalted butter and just taste it before you add any more salt. Because the corn I purchase is naturally sweet, I've never had to add any sugar to this dish. I highly recommend this as a great side dish!

Rating: 3
I thought this was delicious, but it was a little too salty for my taste. Will definitely make it again with less salt. I did not miss the cream at all which makes this recipe all the better.

